<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
When 
<bibRefCitation pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Sydow and Sydow (1915)</bibRefCitation>
published the name 
<taxonomicName class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Hemileia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hemileia scheffleri" order="Pucciniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="scheffleri">Hemileia scheffleri</taxonomicName>
, they attributed it only to Syd., however, the name is clearly based on 
<taxonomicName class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Uredo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Uredo scheffleri" order="Pucciniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="scheffleri">Uredo scheffleri</taxonomicName>
i.e. both names are based on the same type specimen. With the new ICN, this name in 
<taxonomicName class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Hemileia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hemileia" order="Pucciniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Hemileia</taxonomicName>
is the correct name for this species.
</paragraph>
